Key Match Events: San Antonio Spurs defeated the Portland Trail Blazers with a score of 118-105.
Portland Trail Blazers shot nine-of-32 from beyond the 3-point line for a 28 percent clip.
San Antonio Spurs shot 16-of-29 from 3-point range.
Post-Match Reflections: Trail Blazers head coach Chauncey Billups felt his team was 'chasing our tails' for the entire game.
Billups commented on Shaedon Sharpe's return, saying 'I thought Shaedon played really well. He looked comfortable.'
Billups praised his team's defense on Victor Wembanyama, stating 'I thought we did a good job on him.'
Others: Shaedon Sharpe returned to the court for his season debut after recovering from shoulder surgery, scoring 13 points with two rebounds and one assist.
Victor Wembanyama was held to 12 points, eight rebounds, four steals, and three blocks by the Portland defense.
